<%--
    EXAMPLE — area-variant element template (annotated side-by-side)

    Path: themes/<theme>/templates/DNADesign/Elemental/Models/ElementContent_HomeContentElementalArea.ss

    This is the SS4 element template that replaces the SS3 legacy
    `ContentBlock_HomeContent.ss`. The HTML structure is identical —
    only the data-injection variables changed.

    Resolved by SS4 Elemental when:
      - The element is `DNADesign\Elemental\Models\ElementContent`
      - The element's parent ElementalArea is reached via the page's
        `HomeContentElementalArea` has_one relation
    Falls through to `ElementContent.ss` otherwise.

    ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    LEGACY SS3 SOURCE (themes/<theme>/templates/Includes/ContentBlock_HomeContent.ss):
    ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    <div class="$CSSClasses">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="lines"></div>
            <div class="col-md-5"><div class="inner">
                <% if $Title %><h3>$Title</h3><% end_if %>           ← $Title check
                <div class="typography">
                    <% if $Content %><p>$Content.Plain<% end_if %>   ← $Content
                </div>
            </div></div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <% if $Image %><img src="$Image.URL" alt="Title"><% end_if %>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    MIGRATED SS4 — THE FILE BELOW
    ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

    Diff summary (per template-parity-pattern.md cheatsheet):
      • `$CSSClasses` → `$StyleClasses block contentblock`
        Reason: $CSSClasses in SS4 is verbose ("ElementContent BaseElement
        DataObject"); we want the legacy "contentblock block" so the SS3
        CSS still matches. $StyleClasses gives us the CMS-set style
        without the class-hierarchy verbosity.

      • `<% if $Title %>` → `<% if $ShowTitle && $Title %>`
        Reason: Elemental adds a ShowTitle boolean field. The migration
        task sets ShowTitle=1 when the legacy block had a non-empty title;
        respect it here.

      • `$Content` → `$HTML`
        Reason: ElementContent's CMS field is called "Content" but the
        template variable was renamed to $HTML. (The #1 source of "I
        migrated the block but the template shows blank" bugs.)

      • Added `<% if $SubTitle %>` block (optional)
        Reason: If your project added a SubTitle extension to
        ElementContent. Drop if you didn't.

    Nothing else changed. The div nesting, column classes, typography
    div, image wrapper — all identical. Existing CSS works untouched.
--%>

<div class="$StyleClasses block contentblock">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="lines"></div>
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <div class="inner">
                <% if $ShowTitle && $Title %><h3>$Title</h3><% end_if %>
                <% if $SubTitle %><h3>$SubTitle</h3><% end_if %>
                <div class="typography">
                    <% if $HTML %><p>$HTML.Plain<% end_if %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <% if $Image %>
                <img src="$Image.URL" class="img-responsive" alt="$Title">
            <% end_if %>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
